. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl."},{"content":"Add bread, shallot, parsley, basil, salt and pepper and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add salmon and Worcestershire sauce and chop <b>5 sec\/\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Divide and shape salmon mixture into four equal-sized patties (1 in. thick). Create a dimple in the center of patties by pressing down with your fingers to prevent them from rising while cooking. Place a frying pan over medium heat and add oil. Fry patties for 3-4 minutes each side or until golden brown and cooked to desired temperature."},{"content":"Spread bun with Tartar Sauce, add salmon patty and red onion slices and serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Wash lemon and herbs before use.","For a gluten-free salmon patty replace Worcestershire sauce with 1 tsp liquid aminos, (e.g. Bragg)"],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","4 portions"]}